main event: A circular object was observed in wavering flight over Tipp City, Ohio, on 29 Aug 65.
interesting points: The object was yellowish white and moved behind clouds, appearing slightly brighter than the brightest star., The sighting lasted for about 2-5 minutes., The object's course was to the northeast., Echo II was noted in the area around the same time., The report concluded that the object was a satellite (ECHO II).
